====Mathematical formulae====
*Formulae that include mathematical letters, like {{math|x}}, and operators like "&times;" should not use the plain letter "x".  See the ''[[MOS:MATH#Font_formatting|Font formatting]]'' section of the [[MOS:MATH|Manual of Style for mathematics]]. For a comprehensive set of symbols, and comparison between <code>&lt;math&gt;</code> tags and the {{template|math}} template see section  [[Help:Displaying_a_formula#TeX_vs_HTML|''TeX vs HTML'']] in ''[[Help:Displaying a formula|Displaying a formula]]''.

*The '''<code>&lt;math&gt;</code>''' tag typesets using [[MOS:MATH#Typesetting_of_mathematical_formulae|LaTeX markup]], which may render as an image or as HTML, depending on environmental settings.   The <code>&lt;math&gt;</code> tag is best for the complex formula on its own line in an image format.  If you use this tag to put a formula in the line with text, put it in the {{tl|nowrap}} template.

*The '''{{template|math}}''' template [[MOS:MATH#Using_HTML|uses HTML]], and will size-match a serif font, and will also prevent line-wrap.  All templates are sensitive to the "=" sign, so remember to replace <code>=</code> with <code>{{tl|{{=}}}}</code> in template input. Use wikitext <code><nowiki>''</nowiki></code> and <code><nowiki>'''</nowiki></code> inside the {{math}} template, as well other [[Wikipedia:Mathematical_symbols|HTML entities]]. The {{template|math}} template is best for typeset formulas in line with the text. 

